content:
To create a visually appealing and user-friendly comment section for an article about the negative impact of mass tourism and the need for sustainable solutions, you can use HTML along with some basic CSS for styling. Here's a simple implementation:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Comment Section</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f4f4f9;
        }
        .comment-section {
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #fff;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .comment-section h2 {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            color: #333;
        }
        .comment-form {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
        }
        .comment-form input[type="text"],
        .comment-form textarea {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 5px;
            resize: vertical;
        }
        .comment-form input[type="submit"] {
            background-color: #28a745;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 10px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: background-color 0.3s;
        }
        .comment-form input[type="submit"]:hover {
            background-color: #218838;
        }
        .comment-list {
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        .comment {
            border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
            padding-bottom: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        .comment:last-child {
            border-bottom: none;
        }
        .comment-name {
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .comment-text {
            margin-top: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="comment-section">
    <h2>Comments</h2>
    <form class="comment-form">
        <input type="text" name="name" placeholder="Your Name" required>
        <textarea name="comment" rows="4" placeholder="Your Comment" required></textarea>
        <input type="submit" value="Post Comment">
    </form>
    <div class="comment-list">
        <!-- Comments will be displayed here -->
        <div class="comment">
            <div class="comment-name">John Doe</div>
            <div class="comment-text">This article really opened my eyes to the impact of mass tourism. We need to act now!</div>
        </div>
        <!-- More comments can be added here -->
    </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
- **HTML Structure**: The HTML consists of a form with input fields for the user's name and comment, along with a submit button. Below the form, there is a section to display the list of comments.
- **CSS Styling**: Simple CSS is used to style the comment section, making it visually appealing with a clean and modern look. The form elements and comments are styled for better readability and user interaction.
- **Interactivity**: The code provided is static, so it doesn't include functionality for handling form submission or dynamically displaying comments. This would typically require JavaScript and a backend to manage and display submitted comments.

You can enhance this basic structure further by integrating JavaScript for dynamic interactions and using a backend language or framework to handle form submissions and data storage.
